description:
Add benchmark coverage for the CompareNouns function.

## Function signature
```go
func CompareNouns(word1, word2 string) string
```

Compares noun forms, returns 'eq', 's:p', 'p:s', 'p:p', or '' if unrelated.

## Location
Add to `compare_test.go` alongside existing BenchmarkCompare.

## Pattern to follow
```go
func BenchmarkCompareNouns(b *testing.B) {
    benchmarks := []struct {
        name  string
        word1 string
        word2 string
    }{
        {"equal", "cat", "cat"},
        {"singular_plural", "cat", "cats"},
        {"plural_singular", "cats", "cat"},
        {"irregular", "child", "children"},
        {"unrelated", "cat", "dog"},
    }

    for _, bm := range benchmarks {
        b.Run(bm.name, func(b *testing.B) {
            for range b.N {
                inflect.CompareNouns(bm.word1, bm.word2)
            }
        })
    }
}
```

## Verification
```bash
go test -bench=BenchmarkCompareNouns -benchmem ./...
```

## Acceptance criteria
- Benchmark covers equal, singular/plural, plural/singular, irregular, and unrelated cases
- Uses sub-benchmarks with descriptive names
- Includes -benchmem for allocation tracking

